Let $G$ be a countable group and $X$ a Polish space. A continuous action $G \curvearrowright X$ is \emph{topologically amenable} if for every compact subset $K \subseteq X$ there are continuous maps
\begin{equation*}
p_n \colon X \times G \to \bbR_{\ge 0}, \quad n \in \bbN,
\end{equation*}
such that, with the convention $p_{n,x}(\cdot) \coloneqq p_n(x, \cdot)$,
\begin{enumerate}
\item $p_{n,x} \in \ell^1(G)$ and $\| p_{n,x} \|_1 = 1$ for every $n \in \bbN$ and $x\in X$,
\item $\sup_{x \in K} \| g\cdot p_{n,x} - p_{n,gx} \|_1 \to 0$ as $n \to \infty$, for every $g \in G$, and where $g \cdot p_{n,x}(h) = p_{n,x}(g^{-1}h)$.
\end{enumerate}

nodes.proof:
Let $(p_n)_{n \in \bbN}$ is a sequence of maps witnessing topological amenability of $G \curvearrowright X$ for $K \subseteq X$, and define the Borel maps
\begin{align*}
\lambda_n \colon E_G^X &\to \bbR_{\ge 0} \\
(x,y) &\mapsto \sum_{\substack{g \in G \\ g^{-1}x = y}} p_{n,x}(g).
\end{align*}
Then the sequence $\lambda_n$ satisfies the assumption of Lemma \ref{lemma:subgraph_ua} with $E_0 = E_G^X$, $E_1 = E_{\sch(X, S)|_K}$ and $\rho_1 = \rho_{\sch(X, S)|_K}$, hence the graph $\sch(X, S)|_K$ is u-amenable.

